      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BARSBY (5) scored two back at this track then lined up for a hat trick and finished 3.5 metres from the winner in second over 1660m here at the latest run two-and-a-half weeks ago. Meets a comparable field and he can figure in the finish. CALL IT BLING (7) followed a minor placing two runs ago with a win last start by 1.75 metres over 1660m at this circuit despite galloping in the run. Will need a bit of luck negotiating a very wide starting position. Facing a tougher assignment but he is up to the task. RED BULL BERNIE (6) is in the mix following a sixth at his most recent appearance over 1730m at Bathurst. KING BLING (1) won't have any excuses from the favourable draw and shouldn't be discounted lightly.",
